Step 1: Project Overview - Supply Chain Management System
Introduction

Welcome to the Supply Chain Management System Project.
This project demonstrates how a relational database can be used to efficiently manage and analyze supply chain operations. It focuses on handling real-world data related to customers, orders, products, and suppliers using SQL.

Through this project, we build a structured system that ensures smooth data flow, accurate tracking, and better decision-making.

Project Objective

The main objective of this project is to design and implement a robust SQL-based database system.

By completing this project, you will be able to:

Design a relational database schema
Understand relationships between multiple entities
Implement DDL (Data Definition Language) commands
Apply constraints like Primary Keys and Foreign Keys
Perform DML (Data Manipulation Language) operations
Write advanced SQL queries for business analysis
Key Features of the System
Centralized data management system
Efficient tracking of orders and transactions
Strong data integrity using constraints
Optimized query performance
Real-time business insights using SQL queries
Why This Project is Important

In real-world businesses, supply chain management plays a crucial role in operations.

This project helps you:

Understand real industry-level database design
Work with realistic datasets
Improve problem-solving using SQL
Gain practical experience for Data Analyst roles

It bridges the gap between theoretical SQL knowledge and real-world application.

How to Use This Project

This project is divided into structured steps for better understanding:

Step 1: Project Overview

Understand the purpose and structure of the system

Step 2: Dataset & Requirements

Learn about tables, relationships, and business rules

Step 3: SQL Implementation

Create database, tables, and insert data

Step 4: Practice Queries

Solve real-world business problems

Step 5: Solutions & Optimization

Analyze solutions and improve query performance

Conclusion

This project provides a complete understanding of how SQL can be used to manage supply chain data efficiently.
It enhances your ability to design databases, analyze data, and generate meaningful business insights.
